content: As an AI language model, I don't have access to Caltech's current admissions policies, but historically Caltech has prioritized STEM fields, including physics, engineering, mathematics, and computer science, in its admissions process. This is reflected in the rigorous curriculum and research opportunities provided to students in these fields. However, Caltech also values well-rounded applicants who have demonstrated leadership, creativity, and a passion for learning outside of their academic pursuits. It is likely that the current admissions process continues to prioritize these values.
